   Bioethics in NASA

   NASA is deeply committed to ensuring our research, technology
   development and health care adheres to the highest bioethical
   principles. We are establishing a function within the Office of the
   Chief Health and Medical Officer at Headquarters NASA to address
   bioethical considerations for the Agency. The Chief of Bioethics (Care
   and Protection of Research Subjects and Patients) serves as the Agencys
   functional manager to ensure medical practice and research on human and
   animal subjects is conducted safely and in accordance with the highest
   ethical standards. This individual also serves as the principle NASA
   authority and consultant for matters pertaining to bioethics. NASA also
   regularly consults with other nationally respected experts in
   bioethics. For questions concerning bioethics in NASA, the following
   individuals may be contacted:

   Richard S. Williams, M.D.
   Deputy Chief Health and Medical Officer
   Headquarters NASA
   (202) 358-4410
   Send e-mail to: Richard S. Williams, M.D.

   Paul Wolpe, Ph.D.
   Center of Bioethics
   Department of Bioethics
   University of Pennsylvania Health System
   (202) 573-9378

   Baruch Brody, Ph.D.
   Director, Center for Medical Ethics and Health Policy
   Baylor College of Medicine
   (713) 798-3503
